##Against the wind, a shared sleeping platform and the landlord's sun rise

Micro Signal Xincaijing

Function introduction, the recorder of new business, the promoter of New Economy.

-- Yang Jie

Edited by gale

Into January, Zhang Jingwei early began to prepare.

He is a 90-year-old and a landlord on a shared lodging platform such as AIRBNB. Together with his college classmates, he runs 19 bed-and-breakfast rooms scattered around the Xi'an Bell Tower, one of the most popular destinations for tourists.

Around the Spring Festival is the first battle of the year, and is also the peak season that all the landlords look forward to. In line with past practice, the performance around the Spring Festival usually accounts for one-fifth of the annual revenue.

As of January 10, Zhang Jingwei was booked through February on the AIRBNB platform, with daily reservations fully booked. In order to meet this peak period, Zhang Jingwei to his home-stay with enough shampoo, shower GEL and other cleaning supplies, room cleaning, daily necessities, basic security has also been arranged properly.

He is waiting for a good start. If nothing else, in the two months around the Spring Festival, Zhang's room-rate income is about 100,000 yuan a month.

But the sudden outbreak of the original plan to break, like a clock, suddenly issued a "zero" sound. Cancellations on the platform, high rents, property costs, the development of an unknown epidemic, have become a thorn in his side.

One of the bed and breakfast facilities run by Zhang Jingwei

Zhang's story is not unique. The ripple effect of the crisis has disrupted the rhythm of many businesses. Among them, the wine travel industry that is expected to step on a brake suddenly, like domino, bottom-up to the entire industry to bring sudden pressure.

Corporate rescue efforts are also under way, with shared accommodation platforms including AIRBNB, pigger and Tujia Rolling out emergency measures in response to the outbreak to ensure the best interests of landlords and guests.

This sudden event can be said to be a shared accommodation platform business experience.

In tough times, platforms and landlords are waiting for spring and a revival in the industry.

A sudden battle

For Zhang, the shock was almost sudden.

On January 11, he received the first off-order application on the platform, originally scheduled for the second to fifth day of the Lunar New Year booking guests, discussed off-order, around the Spring Festival, this is a rare situation.

The other party was a family of four from Wuhan. They wanted to take their parents on a trip during the Spring Festival. However, the news of pneumonia one after another made them make a decision to cancel the trip. In the perception of the tenants, this can be regarded as a "force majeure factor" , hope that the landlord can be exempted from liability refund.

"It was still more than 10 days away from the New Year, and it was impossible for the house to be empty according to the experience of previous years, " Zhang said. Feeling the other party's concerns, Zhang gave the tenant a full refund directly.

The numbers of cases jumping up and down made him uneasy, but he seemed far away. To be on the safe side, Zhang immediately provided each room with 84 disinfectants and alcohol, and began handing out face masks to incoming guests.

Case One, case two, case N. . . As the epidemic spread, the number of confirmed cases soared, the number of unsubscribe requests rose along with the number of pneumonia cases, and his mood became more and more complex.

UNSUBSCRIBE requests received during the outbreak

On January 15, Zhang closed all room reservations. On the booked date, if the guest does not cancel the order, the normal reception, the other rooms will be closed.

At the same time, under the epidemic, a large number of tourists began to change the itinerary, air tickets, train tickets, hotels, accommodation and other tourism products have a large number of retrogression.

Centralized unsubscribe began to break out, the major platforms also quickly made a response. On January 21st, OTA platforms such as CTRIP, and shared accommodation platforms such as Airbnb, launched their own cancellation policies to provide waivers for eligible landlords and tenants.

On the 22nd alone, Zhang withdrew 17 bookings from his bed-and-breakfast, the day before the city shut down traffic.

The impact of the epidemic goes far beyond unsubscribing. Rental costs, operating costs, the loss of vacant period, are placed in front of the most realistic problems.

Money is one of the few things that can be quantified in a sustained fight against disease and in a changing policy. In an interview, Zhang calculated a sum for Zinccaijing: Aside from the vacancy charge for all the rooms, the cancellation of the order alone amounted to 110,000 yuan.

When the landlord is damaged, abrupt consumption is low tide, make back-end share accommodation platform is under pressure is more tremendous. But in this kind of special occasion, many shared accommodation platform in the protection of the rights and interests of guests at the same time, began to share the risk with the landlord, ease the anxiety of the moment.

Plan B for shared accommodation

Under the sense of urgency, different shared accommodation platform on how to help, what is "help" , there are different notes.

Let Zhang Jingwei and other landlords take comfort in the fact that, in the process, aibiying platform has opened a channel for the cancellation of the "new crown pneumonia epidemic" and the "Love in action" landlord volunteer program, and landlords and tenants can directly self-help to negotiate the cancellation on the APP, at the same time will not affect the landlord related assessment indicators and "super good landlord" qualification.

"It is very important for us that in such an emergency situation, if the platform does not respond in time, some landlords may have the first interest and cause further population movements, " Zhang told Zncaijing.

On February 5, airbnb invested 70 million yuan in a special fund on the basis of the previous free cancellation, making "10 promises" to the landlord tenants, including extending the cancellation period of exemption from liability and financial compensation to the landlord.

In addition to providing financial compensation to landlords who participate in the "Love in action" landlord volunteer program, airbnb has also pledged to provide flow and other resources in the future, one for the mainland region-related weekly monthly rent, warm heart landlord and other related policies are also the first.

In the response of each major shared accommodation platform, airbnb is the first voice, can be regarded as "with the rhythm of the people. ".

AIRBNB is the first to release its "ten promises" to communities

Subsequently, the pig and the road has also issued corresponding help policies, such as a certain amount of financial compensation for housing orders in February, the start of long-term rental home accommodation program, as well as the follow-up flow tilt guarantee.

On the basis of free unsubscribe, in fact, the support policy of each family, around the key words: First, "Free Service fee" ; Second, "Landlord follow-up development.

Until business is back on track, it may be difficult for most landlords to get over it without platform support, and the fee-free move could give landlords some breathing space.

Specifically, AIRBNB is targeting Hubei Housing orders, waiving the service fee until May 1; Tujia is waiving February orders in Hubei; and piglet is targeting nationwide orders for February.

"perception is not big. " Zhang Jingwei, who is based on all three platforms, also expressed his view that February had been a bleak month because of the impact of the epidemic, with virtually no orders.

The battered bed and breakfast industry

For the landlord, the real excitement is in the subsequent flow tilt. During this period, landlords who offer customers a full refund will be labeled as "heart-warming landlords" on the airbnb platform, which aims to increase exposure and other support and incentives after the outbreak.

Zhang was relatively sanguine: "If the platform, for example, raises the exposure of the housing market and gives some other marketing incentives, according to past experience, my housing market is basically fully booked, I believe that the two quarters will be able to make up for the losses during the epidemic, which is the most substantial help. "

Seize the changeless and the changeless

According to statistics from the Ministry of Culture and Tourism of China, during the Spring Festival in 2019, the total number of tourist receptions in China reached 415 million, up 7.6 percent year on year. This year, those losses are being borne by players in the upper, middle and lower reaches of the river.

The crisis has occurred, and the platform and the landlord are in desperate need of a self-help.

The series of policies on shared accommodation platforms, including AIRBNB, is not only a crisis response to the epidemic, but also a measure to ensure the quality of tourism products.

From a short-term point of view, this epidemic has caused an impact on the tourism industry, revenue plunged in the first half of this year, the loss is already a definite situation.

However, from a longer-term perspective, referring to the development of the tourism market in the post-sars era in 2003, coupled with the pent-up demand of many tourists during the Spring Festival, the tourism industry will also have a new opportunity for development after the epidemic.

In 2003, after the end of the SARS epidemic in the first month, the tourism industry ushered in a "retaliatory" rebound, wine and tourism market ushered in a rapid recovery. In July and August of that year, the volume of business of the major tourism organizations increased dramatically, even exceeding the level before the outbreak of SARS.

For the tourism industry, although vulnerable to the external environment, but its core market demand has always been, in this period, the need for the population has grown.

After SARS, the number of tourists grew against the trend

For the shared accommodation platform, it is very important to grasp this opportunity, ensure the quality of tourism products and response efficiency, and ensure the future development of landlords.

Considering the market recovery cycle, in addition to service charges, for larger investment, location better housing, you can temporarily consider doing weekly long rent.

February 8, AIRBNB has launched the first weekly monthly rental activities, warm heart landlord will receive flow support. According to the source, AIRBNB will continue to deepen the activity in the future, including the reduction of platform service fees.

Changes in the external environment need to be keenly aware of the people in the industry, but unchanged is the internal characteristics of the enterprise.

For AIRBNB, the epidemic is a variable, but the community spirit of airbnb remains constant. Long-term followers of the lodging-sharing giant can sense that AIRBNB's cultural construction has brought the platform and the landlord closer and warmer.

During the outbreak, Airbnb Landlord Kenny issued an advocacy letter on various social media platforms and spontaneously United Airbnb community landlords in Wuhan to provide free accommodation for medical staff.

Li Ying, who runs a bed-and-breakfast business in Chiang Mai, took 3,000 disposable surgical masks and 300 pairs of gloves she had received from caring people and spent three days supporting the Simao District People's Hospital in Puer.

Ai Biying Landlord Li Ying sent protective materials to the hospital

Under pressure to make a profit, Zhang also provided his home to Xi'an's health care workers during the Lunar New Year holiday and donated 4,000 face masks to the Wuhan Union Hospital through a fund-raising campaign with university students.

The high cohesion and warmth of the community is also a reflection of the unique cultural values of AIRBNB.

Waiting for spring

In an internal letter obtained by Zinccaijing, Peng Tao, the Chinese President, said: In the Chinese market, Zinccaiying has devoted more resources to building platform capabilities, which also makes it possible to face sudden changes, more flexible allocation of resources to serve the immediate needs of the options.

Second, as a global company, airbnb's unique global advantages also make the organization more resilient and resilient to risks.

In this special period, the platform began to focus on the cultivation of internal skills, improve the basic skills of the team and the battle effectiveness of the organization, better turn crisis into opportunity.

Internal Letter from Peng Tao, president of AIRBNB China

It's not just the platform, it's the landlords.

Today in AIRBNB's residential community, the most discussed topic among landlords is self-help. In the host community, some landlords have already begun to transfer because of financial constraints, but many more are still seeking opportunities in the crisis to prepare for post-epidemic recovery.

In Zhang Jingwei's view, some people retreat, some people enter, risk and opportunity is co-existing, this period of time if the operation is good, can still achieve break-even.

At the same time, among the 10 commitments previously issued by AIRBNB, a landlord training course specifically targeting the epidemic period has also started to fall into place. It has officially launched the AIRBNB Landlord College Channel, one of the areas of greatest concern for landlords, to give instruction or skill.

It's worth noting that the classes that are currently online are all voluntary shares from landlords.

AIRBNB landlord college course

"I was worried at the beginning, but now I think I should take action and use this time to carefully sort out the operation of the real estate, lay a solid foundation and repair the internal work. " AIBIYING LANDLORD MU is still optimistic about the future of the industry after a short period of strength.

For the landlord, the help of the platform is part of it. Now the quiet period, but also a good time to learn and reflect, what is a good-looking room, bed and breakfast should be how to design, good color collocation, what is the spatial structure, this is the bed and breakfast people need to constantly upgrade, draw experience point.

How should landlords grow in the face of the new crown pneumonia epidemic? "there is not a winter that will not pass, and not a spring that will not come. I believe the shared accommodation and tourism sectors will recover and rebound quickly after the outbreak. Through this difficult period, there will be a better spring,"AIRBNB's super-awesome landlord, Kang Jian, concluded in his post.
